  "local_port": 56760,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the scholarships an MBBS student in India?",
  "response": "In India, several scholarships are available for MBBS students to help ease the financial burden of medical education. These scholarships are offered by government bodies, private organizations, and educational institutions. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **Central Sector Scheme of Scholarships for College and University Students**: Offered by the Department of Higher Education, this scholarship supports meritorious students from economically weaker sections.\n\n2. **AISEE (All India Scholarship Entrance Examination)**: This competitive exam provides scholarships to students pursuing medical, engineering, and other professional courses.\n\n3. **Nationwide Education and Scholarship Test (NEST)**: NEST offers scholarships to students from first-year MBBS to postgraduate levels in medical and other fields, based on their performance in the test.\n\n4. **Vidyasaarathi Scholarship by NSDL**: Aimed at supporting students from economically weaker backgrounds, this scholarship covers tuition fees for students pursuing higher education, including MBBS.\n\n5. **Indira Gandhi Single Girl Child Scholarship**: This UGC-funded scholarship is available for single girl children pursuing postgraduate courses, which indirectly benefits those in medical education.\n\n6. **Indian Oil Academic Scholarships**: Indian Oil Corporation offers scholarships to meritorious students pursuing professional courses, including MBBS.\n\n7. **Colgate Scholarship**: Though primarily aimed at school children, older students in professional courses like MBBS can also compete for these scholarships with particular criteria.\n\n8. **ONGC Scholarship for OBC Category**: Oil and Natural Gas Corporation offers scholarships to OBC students pursuing professional degrees at the graduate and postgraduate levels, including MBBS.\n\n9. **FAEA Scholarship**: The Foundation for Academic Excellence and Access provides scholarships for undergraduate studies, including medical courses, to students from economically disadvantaged backgrounds.\n\n10. **K.C. Mahindra Scholarship**: This scholarship is for students pursuing higher education and is open to students showing academic excellence and requiring financial assistance.\n\n11. **National Entrance Screening Test (NEST) Scholarships**: This is another merit-based scholarship after the entrance examination, catering to undergraduate students in various streams, including MBBS, at several institutions across the country.\n\nIt is always advisable for students to check the specific eligibility criteria, application deadlines, and procedures for each scholarship, as these can vary. Additionally, some universities and colleges offer their own scholarships or tuition waiver schemes based on merit and financial need.",
